                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Sao Paulo, March 10: Cia Vale do Rio Doce, the worlds biggest iron-ore producer, won a 66 per cent ore-price increase from Tata Steels Corus unit for shipments from the Carajas mine through the Ponta da Madeira port in northern Brazil. Corus will pay 65 per cent more than last year for iron ore shipped through the Tubarao port in southeastern Brazil.                            
