	 New Delhi, March 10: Maruti Suzuki India has inked a pact with Shriram City Union Finance with an initial allocation of Rs 1,000 crore. The tieup will focus on financing of entry-level cars from the Maruti portfolio, which include the M800, the Omni and the Alto.                            
	 Chennai, March 10: Finance minister P. Chidambaram has said he would inform Parliament on Friday on how the government would compensate banks for the losses incurred on account of the farm loan waiver.                            
	 Chandigarh, March 10: Public sector banks employees have renewed their threat to go on an indefinite strike if the Indian Banks Association failed to accept their demands by May 31.                                                                                                                           
